Class Entry

java.lang.Object
object.Entry
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ExerciseEntry, FoodEntry
public abstract class Entry extends Object implements Cloneable
Represents a generic entry (e.g., food or exercise record) in the system. Each entry belongs to a specific daily plan and records a unique identifier, an entry type, and an optional note.

Subclasses must provide their own logic for calculating calories, displaying entry information, and validating their data.

    • Entry

      public Entry(Entry.EntryType type, String note)
      Creates a new Entry with the specified type and note. A unique identifier is automatically generated.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of entry (planned, planned complete, or recorded)
      note - an optional note or description for the entry

  • Method Details

    • calculateCalories

      public abstract double calculateCalories()
      Calculates the calories for this entry.

      Implementations must provide logic based on the type of entry, e.g., food entries calculate from quantity and gram, exercise entries calculate from duration and intensity.

      Returns:
      the calculated calories (in kcal) for this entry

    • getDisplayName

    • getDisplayInfo

      public abstract String getDisplayInfo()

      Returns:
      a descriptive string containing details about the entry

    • validate

      public abstract void validate()
      Validates the state of this entry.

      Subclasses must implement checks to ensure that their data is logically valid. For example, food entries must have a portion > 0, and exercise entries must have a duration > 0.

      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the entry contains invalid data

    • updateFrom

      public void updateFrom(Entry newEntry)

    • clone

      public Entry clone()
      Creates a copy of this entry with a new unique identifier.

      The cloned entry is treated as a new record, while preserving the data from the original.

      Returns:
      a new Entry instance with copied values and a new unique identifier
      Throws:
      AssertionError - if cloning is not supported
